UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2284
1 certified adoptive or foster home under subsections (1) and (2) of this section;
2 or
3 (b) Register each adult household member of a certified adoptive or foster home
4 under subsections (1) and (2) of this section in the rap back system.
5 (5) If a child is placed and resides in a fictive kin home for more than seventy-two (72)
6 hours, the Cabinet for Health and Family Services shall take action, including but
7 not limited to the following:
8 (a) Provide information on how to recognize and report child abuse or neglect;
9 and
10 (b) Ensure that, within the first five (5) days of a child under the age of five (5)
11 years old being placed in a fictive kin home, the fictive kin has completed a
12 one (1) time training course of one and one-half (1.5) hours of training
13 covering the prevention and recognition of pediatric abusive head trauma, as
14 defined in KRS 620.020.
15 (6) The Cabinet for Health and Family Services shall promulgate an administrative
16 regulation in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A to implement this section.
